snippet.textDisplay:
Emotions were already at a high level in the Staples Center yesterday (The House Kobe built) where just a few miles away, six or seven hours before was the tragic accident that killed Kobe, Gianna and their seven friends. Crowds formed outside in memorium to Kobe and Gigi as Grammy guests were arriving. The whole awards event went on with very heavy hearts and then Demi's song on top of that, Wow! I feel her personal story behind this song coupled with losing a friend and legend just hours before really effected the performance.
Im not a huge Demi fan but I respect her and love her work and this performance brought out some big emotions in me last night.

snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve been a Lovatic since Camp Rock and I’m ngl, I’ve teared up every time I rewatch this performance. You can just tell how much emotion, heart, and soul she puts into this song.
I love how, like Sober, it was just stripped back with a piano and raw vocals.
Not only that, but people with all types of backgrounds and professions would find this song relatable. I understand that especially in the entertainment industry, as luxurious as it appears, it can actually be quite a lonely world.
I’m glad that she got a standing ovation, I’m so proud of her, she really deserved it
We’re all here, we’re all present, and we’re all listening
I also just found out that it was recorded 4 days before her overdose and my heart is just aching and breaking for her, I just wish I could give her a big hug
